com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.core.model.implementation
Class ModelGenerator

java.lang.Object
  com.csvanefalk.keytestgen.core.model.implementation.ModelGenerator
All Implemented Interfaces:
IModelGenerator
public class ModelGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
implements IModelGenerator

Given that a client does not specify anything else, KeYTestGen2 will default to this implementation of IModelGenerator for the purpose of instantiating path conditions.

This particular implementation makes use of SMT solvers in order to facilitate model generation. The pathcondition to be instantiated is translated into the SMT-LIB2 language, and the KeY SMT interface is subsequently invoked in order to find an assignment of variables that satisfy the pathcondition (if such an assignment exits).

The set of assignments found are further processed into an instance of Model, which constitutes the final representaiton of the model.
